<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFBEFFC0C676037F96D6FAC4" authority="Wang &amp; Li, 2020" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2020" box="[622,1021,1292,1319]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="menglunensis">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFBEFFC0C676037F9603FAC4" box="[622,808,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">R. menglunensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFBEFFC0C72A037F96D6FAC4" author="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q." box="[818,1021,1292,1319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="398" pagination="25 - 57" refId="ref8660" refString="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q. (2020) On eight species of jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys, 909, 25 - 57. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 909.47137" type="journal article" year="2020">
Wang &amp; Li, 
<quantity id="006D9B7FFFBEFFC0C7DD037E96D6FAC4" box="[965,1021,1292,1318]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1308" pageId="9" pageNumber="398" unit="in" value="2020.0">2020</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in epigynal morphology but can be differentiated by the orientation of the copulatory openings—the scletorized u-shaped margin, oriented along the longitudinal axis (crescent-like in 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFBEFFC0C60E032797E6FA8C" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2020" box="[534,717,1364,1390]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="menglunensis">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFBEFFC0C60E032797E6FA8C" box="[534,717,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">R. menglunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (cf. 
<figureCitation id="5FAE2A1FFFBEFFC0C713032696A3FA8C" box="[779,904,1364,1390]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–41" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,181,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 36–41. Somatic morphology and copulatory organs of Rhene mus (Simon, 1889), holotype female: 36—dorsal view; 37, 40—epigyne, ventral view; 38—habitus, lateral view; 39—ditto, front view; 41—label. Scale bars: (37, 40) 0.2 mm; (39) 0.5 mm; (36, 38) 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450931/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">Figs 37, 40</figureCitation>
with fig. 14A in 
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFBEFFC0C05F03279009FA8C" author="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q." box="[1095,1314,1364,1391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="398" pagination="25 - 57" refId="ref8660" refString="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q. (2020) On eight species of jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys, 909, 25 - 57. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 909.47137" type="journal article" year="2020">Wang &amp; Li (2020))</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C72A369AFFBEFFC0C4DF030A966CF988" blockId="9.[151,1437,1219,1679]" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFBEFFC0C4DF030A9744FA70" bold="true" box="[199,623,1399,1426]" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">
Supplementary description. 
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFBEFFC0C60003059744FA70" bold="true" box="[536,623,1399,1426]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">Female</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="182E8838FFBEFFC0C665030A97CDFA71" box="[637,742,1400,1427]" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">holotype</typeStatus>
). Body length: 4.68; carapace: 1.98 long, 1.91 wide; abdomen: 2.70 long, 1.82 wide. Carapace brown, covered with pale hairs; eye field light brown; posterior eyes surrounded by black patches (
<figureCitation id="5FAE2A1FFFBEFFC0C57B03B29492FA39" box="[355,441,1472,1499]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–41" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,181,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 36–41. Somatic morphology and copulatory organs of Rhene mus (Simon, 1889), holotype female: 36—dorsal view; 37, 40—epigyne, ventral view; 38—habitus, lateral view; 39—ditto, front view; 41—label. Scale bars: (37, 40) 0.2 mm; (39) 0.5 mm; (36, 38) 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450931/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
). Eye measurements: AME 0.38, ALE 0.18, PME 0.05, PLE 0.14, AER 1.29, PER 1.93, EFL 1.27. Clypeus height 0.03. Chelicerae 0.52 long. Sternum oval, light brown. Chelicerae yellow-brown; labium and maxillae light brown. Legs yellowish brown (
<figureCitation id="5FAE2A1FFFBEFFC0C6DD007A9659F9C0" box="[709,882,1544,1570]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–41" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,181,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 36–41. Somatic morphology and copulatory organs of Rhene mus (Simon, 1889), holotype female: 36—dorsal view; 37, 40—epigyne, ventral view; 38—habitus, lateral view; 39—ditto, front view; 41—label. Scale bars: (37, 40) 0.2 mm; (39) 0.5 mm; (36, 38) 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450931/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">Figs 36, 38, 39</figureCitation>
). Abdomen yellow, without any pattern (
<figureCitation id="5FAE2A1FFFBEFFC0C123007A90A4F9C1" box="[1339,1423,1544,1571]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–41" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,181,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 36–41. Somatic morphology and copulatory organs of Rhene mus (Simon, 1889), holotype female: 36—dorsal view; 37, 40—epigyne, ventral view; 38—habitus, lateral view; 39—ditto, front view; 41—label. Scale bars: (37, 40) 0.2 mm; (39) 0.5 mm; (36, 38) 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450931/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
); venter yellowish uniformly. Spinnerets yellowish. Epigyne with a pair of medio-lateral copulatory openings and a median epigynal pocket in the posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="5FAE2A1FFFBEFFC0C6A000229610F988" box="[696,827,1616,1642]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–41" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,181,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[179,1408,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 36–41. Somatic morphology and copulatory organs of Rhene mus (Simon, 1889), holotype female: 36—dorsal view; 37, 40—epigyne, ventral view; 38—habitus, lateral view; 39—ditto, front view; 41—label. Scale bars: (37, 40) 0.2 mm; (39) 0.5 mm; (36, 38) 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450931/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="398">Figs 37, 40</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
